The paper focuses on generating explanations for human-robot teaming, which involves both human-computer interaction (HCI) and robotics (RO). Therefore, cs.HC and cs.RO are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of algorithms and quantifications, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (LG). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) to generate explanations, which falls under the sub-category of computational linguistics (CL).
